description.1: Torch and Toro must put the kibosh on a hypnotist who is turning his powers of persuasion into a dark art!
description.2: Irony in its purest form! A man aims to kill his wife, but their bodies are then fused together!
description.3: Death has found his very own garden...and it's on Earth.
description.4: Byrrah returns to topple Namor's rule over Atlantis!
description.7: Behold an alien abduction, a lunar colony, a shocking hypnosis, and more!
description.8: The hour of nuclear war may be at hand -- the Vulture and his bad guy syndicate are nearly finished with their construction of super atomic bombs!
description.9: Lorna must determine why the creatures in her domain have become unruly! A hunting party might be to blame!
description.10: A scientist inadvertently causes a crop of mutations in a few employees at a test site! A man murders his wife in cold blood, and her corpse faces a gruesome fate.
description.13: Groups of "young" hoodlums are creating quite a handful for the Torch and Toro!
description.15: A husband and wife are both vampires...and keeping that secret from each other!
description.16: In these spooky tales? Behold a space armada, a Martian spy, the last man on Earth, and more!
description.17: Mamalu, the Voodoo goddess lives! And she's seeking vengeance on non-believer Lorna the Jungle Queen!
description.19: In yet another werewolf story, a man who shoots dogs for fun is struck down by a lycanthropic curse!
description.20: Greg Knight takes a boorish stance on animal rights, and Lorna swoops in to put the chauvinist in his place! Should Lorna fail, her animal family may become cruelly treated circus acts!
description.21: The Human Torch returns to crime-fighting after years in confinement!
description.22: An unlucky man stumbles into a land where undead souls hold him hostage!
description.23: A mysterious graveyard yields an extraterrestrial secret. Plus, a mission to Mars, a marooned crew, and more!
description.27: A race of subterranean lizard-people employs a representative who is less than diplomatic with humanity! Plus, a big game sports hunter is set on taking home a werewolf…
description.28: Meet a visitor from Pluto, a man who knows everything, and a man-eating lion! Yikes!
description.31: Can a witch truly fall in love? When an unwitting man is at the mercy of a love-struck witch, he learns new meaning in the phrase, "Hell Hath No Fury Like a Woman Scorned!"
description.32: What is behind a voice that can kill? Plus, take a voyage to the moon and be witness to a murder by hypnotism!
description.33: Lorna is a captive of the Lost City! After discovering coinage from an ancient civilization, Lorna and M'Tuba suspect that residents from this lost world may still be alive...
description.34: In a spin on the ‘Frankenstein’ story, the monster goes on a shambling hunt for a companion, but is met with only rejection and hate.
description.35: Stan Lee pens the "The Graymoor Ghost", "Checkmate!", "The Corpse" and more, in this riveting anthology issue written by a Marvel legend!
description.36: A medium plays an 'undead' prank on another medium in order to draw away business and drum up her own.
description.37: A vampire attacks! Plus, meet a living ball of fire, an immortal alien, and more!
description.38: More jungle adventures starring Lorna the Jungle Queen! This time, she's facing off against the Killer Rogue, the Head-Hunters, and more!
description.39: The origin story of a young girl that learned to tame the wilds of the African jungle, and who would later become...Lorna, the Jungle Queen!
description.40: A man is physically haunted by the spirit of a man he murdered! Plus, a 2005 Space Odyssey sends humanity to Venus… but its atmosphere is far from hospitable.
description.41: A magician does a classic trick with his wife as his volunteer, but the magic proves too real this time!
description.42: Two sword swallowers agree to a duel, the present meets a time traveler, and a future of machines is introduced in the pages of these shocking stories!
description.45: An angered scientist, (who obviously did not read Frankenstein), learns a crucial lesson about man playing God.
description.46: A family feud chills over with devastating consequences! Plus, meet a cursed ragdoll and a murderous farmer!
description.47: What if… Stalin were a vampire? The first of many supernatural tales plays a game of revisionist history! An interplanetary message from a beautiful woman sends a bored intellectual on a journey across the stars!
description.48: Intolerance leads to death in the first of our creepy, far-out tales! Then, a man goes on the trail to find proof of werewolves, but gets way more than he bargained for!
description.50: A strongman seeking even more strength becomes invincible from a magic serum -- which also prevents antibiotics from taking effect.
description.51: Strange tales of startling suspense from the 1950s of Marvel! A rampaging robot, an army of flying saucers, a deadly witch-hunt, and more!
description.54: A tale from the future… of 1998! A vampire has an unusual method for building a ‘blood bank’, while a spy confuses his contact for his target! Plus, a jealous dancer pays the ultimate price when she threatens her competition…
description.55: Don't go digging for treasure, a ghost may emerge to protect its bounty!
description.56: Encounter a world-conquering machine, a small town mystery, and an unexpected mass murderer! Plus, more strange tales ahead!
description.59: A Match Made in Heaven! A man who serially murders his wives, marries a woman who murders her husbands. Who will come out on top?
description.60: A scientist learns how to raise the dead, a boy obtains a book of curses, a ghost sells his soul, and more!
description.61: Love is a toxic game in this collection of spooky, anthology tales! A woman tries to off her husband with disastrous results, while a scaredy-cat librarian turns out to be a monster! Plus, a prison nightmare!
description.62: Prisoners are delighted to see their keeper thrown into the asylum with them!
description.63: More startling spooks coming your way! In this issue, behold a witch's curse, a tragic love triangle, and a man who walks through walls!
description.67: What is the curse of the Grinning Skulls? Plus, will you receive a visit from the spirit of King Midas?
description.69: Karma works in mysterious ways! Owners of an inn murder their guests in order to steal their money. This arrangement can't last forever though...
description.70: A person duels with Death himself! Plus, a burglary spawns a terrible curse, alien scientists, and more!
description.75: In this issue? A love potion turns deadly, a midnight grave robbing, a doomed sea voyage, and more!
description.76: A murderer runs from the police and finds himself in a bar. He seems to be alone with just a bartender until the ghosts of those he's killed keep him company.
description.77: Strange tales of startling suspense from the 1950s of Marvel! A deal with the devil, a walking skeleton, a watery grave, and more!
description.79: We've all heard the playground saying, "step on a crack and break your mother's back". But what if for one young lad, the saying goes: "step on a crack, have the Earth swallow you whole"?
description.80: Be careful what you wish for! Tired of being weak and scrawny, a man purchases a potion to magically make him strong. Will he live to see the consequences?
description.81: A man hits on a 'taken' woman and ends up on the wrong side of Death himself!
description.83: A failed actor makes a devastating, and final, bid for fame. And it's his biggest audience yet!
description.85: Someone decides to steal flowers from burial sites, until the dead come to take back what's rightfully theirs.
description.86: An undead spooktacular! A Hungarian village of vampires rejects one of their half-human citizens.
description.90: Before there was Ego...What happens when humankind discovers that Earth's moon is actually a Living Planet?
description.92: A dejected scientist turns to the occult to uncover the secrets of time travel.
description.93: A wily professor believes that he has enough advantage against the United States to become the country's supreme overlord...until his alien weapon turns the table and attacks him!
description.94: After breaking his neck, a man believes that he has cheated death...until he realizes his shadow is missing!
description.95: From the planet Uranus, Matthew Grayson sends his son to Earth to see if a new magician's abilities could be useful to the world of universal science.
description.96: A pack of venomous snakes is bumping off employees at a zoo one by one -- BOB GRAYSON investigates...even though he hates snakes.
description.97: An alien race unleashes some strange superweapons on Earth in the form of eggs...not only do they reek to high heaven, when broken they release a toxic gas!

6.text: What happens when the Mightiest Man in the Universe loses his memory? A devastating formula is created -- and now citizens are losing their memory too!

12.text: The first appearance of Micky Moran, A.K.A. Marvelman! And in his first issue, the Mightiest Man in the Universe takes on an atomic bomb!

49.text: Corporal Young sees through the eyes of his Chinese POWs when it comes to their repatriation. Pfc. Howard Wicowzki finds he is never alone on the battlefield.

57.text: Tales from the battlefield…across the ages! Richard the Lion-Hearted forges a new crusade against the sinister Saladin! On "Hopeless Hill", Sgt. Dimock struggles to maintain the morale of his men. A cinema star pays a visit to the troops!

58.text: Professor Prael’s resolve is tested like never before when he finds himself kidnapped by communists after being lured to East Berlin!

64.text: An animated history of Benito Mussolini’s rise and fall during WWII! Plus, the U.S. Air Force tips off a Korean village to a bombing that’s set to take place the next day.

66.text: A North Korean captain escalates a conflict between a local farming village and some Americans. Five of America’s best engineers sneak behind enemy lines to incapacitate a power plant.

71.text: A minefield poses an extreme threat to an unsuspecting group of G.I.s. Will Tracy be able to warn his company in time?

74.text: Proving that every individual life matters, a brave private rescues a wounded bird from a combat zone.

78.text: A “clean-up” patrol wipes a small village of all North Korean snipers and combatants!

82.text: A private named Willie takes some bad advice from an incompetent soldier. A recently drafted cook has no desire to be in the midst of battle…until he can no longer avoid the conflict!

87.text: Marty and Lt. Carey learn the hard way that North Korea upholds a very different code of “honor” when it comes to warfare.

89.text: From the frontlines of the Korean War! Five soldiers band together in a foxhole, while a soldier’s wife back in the States reconciles with a decision that connects to her husband’s death. This is War Adventures on the Battlefield!

99.text: A special one-shot featuring Thing, Doctor Strange, Human Torch and more!
